data.chText: 文艺复兴（欧洲14、15和16世纪时，人们以古希腊罗马的思想文化来繁荣文学艺术）
data.enText: the period in Europe during the 14th, 15th and 16th centuries when people became interested in the ideas and culture of ancient Greece and Rome and used these influences in their own art, literature, etc.

data.chText: （某一学科或艺术形式等衰落后的）复兴
data.enText: a situation when there is new interest in a particular subject, form of art, etc. after a period when it was not very popular

word_means: 文艺复兴(欧洲14、15和16世纪时，人们以古希腊罗马的思想文化来繁荣文学艺术)
simple_means.memory_skill: re 一再 + nai 出生 + ss + ance 表情况 → 一再出生 → 复兴，新生

means: 文艺复兴(欧洲14、15和16世纪时，人们以古希腊罗马的思想文化来繁荣文学艺术)
(某一学科或艺术形式等衰落后的)复兴

tr: the revival of learning and culture
the period of European history at the close of the Middle Ages and the rise of the modern world
a cultural rebirth from the 14th through the middle of the 17th centuries

value.def: The Renaissance was the period in Europe, especially Italy, in the 14th, 15th, and 16th centuries, when there was a new interest in art, literature, science, and learning.

example.tran: 伦敦美术馆里文艺复兴时期的杰作

example.ex: Science took a new and different turn in the Renaissance.
example.tran: 科学在文艺复兴时期发生了新的转变。

value.def: If something experiences a renaissance, it becomes popular or successful again after a time when people were not interested in it.

example.ex: Popular art is experiencing a renaissance...
They gathered to protest against the renaissance of the extreme right.
example.tran: 他们聚集起来抗议极右势力的复活。

trans: 非洲复兴(非洲在经济和文化方面将出现巨大发展的时期，有人认为这一趋势始于20世纪末)
文艺复兴人，全才人(尤指写作和绘画方面多才多艺的人)
